This paper deals with wireless networks and their optimization, which falls under the category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers time-varying channels and power adaptation, which are topics related to Information Theory (cs.IT). The proposed algorithm is designed to minimize the Age of Information (AoI), which is a metric used in control systems (cs.SY). The paper also uses numerical simulations, which could fall under the category of Machine Learning (cs.MA) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
